* A TimerStat object stores a count and a time.
 *
 * @more
 * When possible, the other APIs in this package avoid requiring a TimerStat
 * object to be constructed, even internally, but the getTimers method on
 * {@link android.os.health.HealthStats} does require TimerStat objects.

variables.name: CREATOR
variables.comment: * The CREATOR instance for use by aidl Binder interfaces.

methods.name: public void writeToParcel(Parcel out, int flags)
methods.comment: * Write this TimerStat object to a parcel.

methods.name: public void setCount(int count)
methods.comment: * Set the count for this timer.

methods.name: public int getCount()
methods.comment: * Get the count for this timer.

methods.name: public void setTime(long time)
methods.comment: * Set the time for this timer in milliseconds.

methods.name: public long getTime()
methods.comment: * Get the time for this timer in milliseconds.
